<br>
Starlett - 61 Wizard - Vazaelle - Secret Keepers <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=skirren>Skirren</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/10/03 12:08 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> my pov</span><hr size=1> I'll use ToV as an example destination here, yes basic poop.<br>
<br>
<br>
Getting there from here:<br>
--------------------------<br>
You are expected to port everyone to the raid, and make sure they can get there fast.<br>
<br>
You get to pick everyone up from the nexus, invis, levitate them, then port to CS, then run to SG, wait for them all, then evac across [cause they are too lazy to run], zone to WW, levi them, invis the KoS ppl. Disband, and go pick up another grp if needed. Yay fun.<br>
<br>
Buffs:<br>
------<br>
Assuming you aren't a group leader (or have to ask for buffs etc), you will only need to Spellshield those who require it - usually no one, lucked out here, play gems for a while. Sometimes it falls on us to crap buff, bust out see invis, vision shift etc, luckily we aren't a buffing class, and can pretty much go afk the entire time, or talk it upon sw.graffe. <br>
<br>
Targets:<br>
--------<br>
Once mobs in camp, nuke, and make sure to not get aggro, rinse repeat till mobs are dead, if you get summoned don't run away too far, just back up till the tank acquires aggro again, use concussion etc.<br>
<br>
Get everyone home:<br>
----------------------<br>
Wether the raid is over or ppl need to leave early, unless they can gate, or they are too lazy to gate, you will be TL'ing them. Teleport is a good help for after the raid, tho while casting it ppl will still spamm you with requests for a tl to bind/nexus/thier favorite spot.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
You can pretty much macro the entire thing, /pause XX,/cast X then a concussions etc. <br>
<br>
I can't think of much else atm, just kill the mobs that need killed, if they call burn, burn a mob down quickly [not talking mb here], gaters are the devil. Really we get off lucky during raids, don't have to buff, don't have to heal your grp and the MT, just pure damage. Have to handle travel, that's about it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hibashira>Hibashira</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 470<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/10/03 10:47 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: my pov</span><hr size=1> This is my personal bit.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">In general:</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--><br>
- Always have TL port fragments available.<br>
- Always have Hate/Sky stones in bank.<br>
- Have all the port/evac/TL spells, including the AE TL.<br>
- Get concussion.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">Before raid:</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--><br>
- know how CoH works and know how to set it up quickly<br>
- be willing to change your bind spot<br>
- knows how all the zones are connected and be ready to give directions<br>
- invis KoS people before porting<br>
- if you zone fast and other porters zone slow, do multiple trips, pick up more than your share of people<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">During raid:</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--><br>
- shut up<br>
- don't whine (see shut up above)<br>
- don't run around<br>
- know what spells land on what mobs<br>
- don't out aggro MT<br>
- use concussion<br>
- nuke till a mob turns, then stop<br>
- if a mob doesn't turn, continue to nuke until its almost dead, then stop<br>
- if your nuke kills a mob, you are wasting mana<br>
- don't show off with high aggro nukes<br>
- don't ask to be rezzed, the clerics are busy, they'll rezz you when they are ready<br>
- make sure all melees got out before gating<br>
- did I mention shut up?<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">After raid</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--><br>
- don't ask for reimbursement for the port chips, its petty <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=328193"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.geocities.com/hibashirasakai/HibashiraNewHalfSize.txt"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hibashira>Hibashira</A> at: 6/10/03 11:57 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=starlettwiz>StarlettWiz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/11/03 11:05 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: my pov</span><hr size=1> Both very helpful.  Thank you. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nilbogrellik>Nilbog Rellik</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/19/03 8:15 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: my pov</span><hr size=1> A lot of times when my guild raids, we set up port chains.  Using ToV for an example:  wizzie/druid ports group from Nexus to CS then gates back to Nexus.  Group runs to Siren's Grotto.  Next wizzie/druid picks up the group and evacs across SG, then gates back to the CS/SG line.  3rd person sits in WW to invis/SOW/lev people for the run to ToV.  Works real well and moves people fast.  Just need to make sure the person evaccing across SG binds himself in CS at the SG line. <p><br>
